race.comment: Cracking edition of the Strathalbyn Cup. SNOOPY NOW (1) is racing in career best form and will appreciate getting some slight weight relief. Keeps his regular hoop in Murtagh, who knows him so well. Rock-hard fit and is sure to be fighting out the finish. KOMACHI (2) finished full of running when getting the job done over 1800m at headquarters on December 27. Freshened with 36 days, keeping the legs ticking over with a solid trial here. Yet to be tested at this trip but is expected to handle it. KIRKLISTON BLU (3) is back somewhere near his best and loves the 2000m. Will land in front, or somewhere close to it and be in this for a very long way. Can steal it if left alone. COORONG TYCOON (10) sets up perfectly for this after savaging the line over this journey at Murray Bridge. Peaking now and is a genuine threat. DUAL FUEL (6) doesn't win out of turn but owns peaks that stack right up. Worth keeping safe.
